    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\n`:h vim.api.nvim_buf_attach` does not bring the user to the documentation for `:h nvim_buf_attach()`.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nGenerating helptags linking the various `vim.api.*` to the corresponding `nvim_*` function documentation would help.\r\n\r\nBfredl also mentionned that having `vim.api.nvim_` as an alias for `vim.api` would provide more useful results when performing `:help api.vim.n<tab>`.\r\n\r\n`:help vim.loop.sp<tab>` finding `uv.spawn()` would be a great improvement too.\r\n\r\nThere's also `vim.fn.foo() -> foo()` and `vim.cmd.foo -> :foo`.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "```lua\r\n-- in vim core\r\nvim.help.on_helptags = function(ns, cb)\r\n  -- ... registers this cb to a namespace\r\nend\r\n\r\n-- In user plugin\r\n\r\nvim.help.on_helptags(\"my_plugin\", function(taglist)\r\n  local result = {}\r\n  for _, tag in ipairs(taglist) do\r\n    table.insert(result, tag)\r\n\r\n    if vim.startswith( tag.name, \"nvim_buf_\") then\r\n      local generated = vim.deepcopy(tag)\r\n      generated.name = \"vim.api.\" .. tag.name\r\n      table.insert(result, generated)\r\n    end\r\n  end\r\n\r\n  return result\r\nend)\r\n```\r\n\r\nPosting here so I don't forget to write anything here later.",
