            "body": "> Expected behavior: Generating helptags linking ...\r\n\r\nWe skipped to this solution (XY problem), but it might not be needed :)\r\n\r\n# Proposal\r\n\r\nWe want `:help vim.api.nvim_buf_attach` to match `:nvim_buf_attach`. Can we enhance `K` and `:help` to have more permissive matching? Partial matching _already_ works, e.g. `:help formatexpr` matches the tag `'formatexpr'`.\r\n\r\n- As an 80% solution, we could very easily trim `vim.api.` or any `x.[y.[â€¦]]` prefix as a fallback when there is no more-precise match.\r\n    - Are there other \"trimmings\" that could be performed to find a match ?\r\n    - Other special cases (`vim.cmd.foo => :foo`, `vim.loop => uv`) can be special-cased in `ex_help`.\r\n- Alternative: should 'keywordprg' apply to interactive `:help` ?",
